title: City Inside/Out: Council Edition - August 2019
description: How will a fight between the Seattle City Council and Mayor Jenny Durkan regarding the sweetened-beverage tax impact the City's budget this fall? Should Seattle's over-budget streetcar program get a $9-million loan? And, what is the Council working on to help missing and murdered indigenous women? Councilmembers Debora Juarez, Lisa Herbold, and Teresa Mosqueda join host Brian Callanan to discuss these topics and more on Council Edition.
